.TH "do_abort" 9 "do_abort" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_abort \- abort the currently established nexus by going to MESSAGE OUT phase and sending an ABORT message.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_abort
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *instance "  ","
.BI "unsigned int can_sleep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "instance" 12
relevant scsi host instance
.IP "can_sleep" 12
1 or 0 when sleeping is permitted or not, respectively
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative error code on failure.
